HEADWORD: Enervation
<hw>En`er*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enervatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧nervation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of weakening, or reducing strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being weakened; effeminacy.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enervative</ent>⟦br⟧
